The direction vectors of the lines are $\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -7 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -7 \end{pmatrix},$ so the lines are parallel.

The distance between the lines is the magnitude of the difference of the translation vectors, which is
\[\left\| \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -3 \end{pmatrix} - \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -5 \end{pmatrix} \right\| = \left\| \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix} \right\| = \boxed{\sqrt{5}}.\] The answer is: \sqrt{5}

