Then $\sin \theta = \frac{5}{13},$ so $\theta = \arcsin \frac{5}{13}.$  By Pythagoras, the adjacent side is $\sqrt{13^2 - 5^2} = 12,$ so $\cos \theta = \boxed{\frac{12}{13}}.$ The answer is: \frac{12}{13}

